#   POST tickets: commit / fast-forward / push

`be post` advances the current branch — worktree→repo commit and/or fast-forward push, recursing into mounted submodules. Tickets below tighten its commit-message handling, push transports, and no-op reporting. Each entry is one active ticket with its live state; an entry drops off once the whole ticket lands (landed commits stay on the board's POST line). The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [POST-006] — `POSTCFLCT` false-fires on conflict-marker strings in tracked source comments/literals (e.g. `sniff/PATCH.c:339`), forcing a blunt `--force`. Recognize only the real WEAVE output shape, not any inline `<<<<…||||…>>>>` occurrence.
 -  [POST-019] — an internal gitlink-bump `put:` banner (`staged 1 put row(s)`) leaks into the MIDDLE of `be post` when a submodule advanced; the bump already shows as `mod <sub>` in the parent post rows. Suppress the standalone put banner for the internal path. Surfaced by [POST-018]/[BE-005].
POST-021 (git-scheme push `BNOROOM` — BASS exhaustion: per-commit walk scratch never
rewound + unused walk buffer; skip it, route the walk through try(), size pack buffers)
landed `387a6f99`; `test/post/46`. POST-022 (sub-push wrecked output: bare per-row label
+ full-history dump) subsumed + fixed by [BE-007] `1a006d08`; `test/post/48`.
POST-020 (git-push post path raw-printf'd `sniff: N change(s)` + the keeper
synthetic-coordinate notice → both now ride `post:` ROWS) landed `8c7f5f3a`; repro
`test/post/25-dot-branch-no-git-wire`, `post/13` grep repointed.
POST-018 (`be post`/`be put` confirmations bypassed the shared ROWS banner) landed
`95252ffd` + `0ac49e6a` (put:/post: banner on stdout). POST-017 (refused `be post` was non-atomic — POSTCFLCT scan ran mid-pack-feed, so
`KEEPPackClose` persisted orphan objects + a rewritten idx before refusing; hoisted all
validation to a pre-flight before any store write) landed `f5b41282`; `test/post/42`.
Follow-up still open: `be`-level scan-before-sub-recursion ordering (`DISPATCH.c:446`).

